# Fortress Simulator

A browser-based colony simulation game using Phaser 3 game engine. Players manage a small colony, construct buildings, gather resources, and ensure the survival of their colonists.

## Features

- Top-down 2D view with sprite-based graphics
- Resource gathering and management (food, wood, stone, metal)
- Build and upgrade different types of buildings
- Colonists with needs, stats and autonomous behaviors
- Day/night cycle with time-based events
- Camera controls for navigating the game world

## Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/fortress_sim.git
cd fortress_sim

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Install canvas package (for placeholder assets)
npm install canvas

# Generate placeholder assets
node src/assets/create_placeholders.js

# Start development server
npm start
```

## Controls

- WASD or Arrow Keys: Move camera
- Mouse Wheel: Zoom in/out
- Left Click: Select units or buildings
- Right Click: Command selected unit to move
- B or H: Toggle house building mode
- F: Toggle farm building mode 
- W: Toggle workshop building mode

## Development

This project uses:
- Phaser 3 for game engine
- Webpack for bundling
- Babel for transpiling
- ESLint for linting

Run `npm run build` to create a production build in the `dist` folder.

wsl -d ubuntu

